    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.8.0-dev-750-g68ec497d5\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo (lua api)\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 12.0.1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.24.4\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color-italic\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo\n\n### How to reproduce the issue\n\nCreate a lua-file with this content. Then run it via `:source %` and save the buffer `:w`. \r\n\r\n```lua\r\nlocal group = vim.api.nvim_create_augroup(\"windows-test\", { clear = true })\r\n\r\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"BufWritePost\", {\r\n  group = group,\r\n  callback = function()\r\n    local buf = vim.api.nvim_create_buf(false, false)\r\n\r\n    vim.api.nvim_buf_set_lines(buf, -1, -1, false, { \"Hello there!\" })\r\n    vim.api.nvim_open_win(buf, true, {\r\n      relative = \"win\",\r\n      win = vim.api.nvim_get_current_win(),\r\n      width = 30,\r\n      height = 4,\r\n      col = 2,\r\n      row = 2\r\n    })\r\n  end\r\n})\r\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nUsing `true` as the second argument for `nvim_open_win`, I expect the new window to be entered. It works as expected when moving those lines outside the callback.\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nThe cursor stays in the window and does not enter the floating window.",
